<HEADLINE>
<P>
DONALD A. WIEDMANN; FORMER OFFICER OF REALTORS' ASSN. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Donald A. Wiedmann, 60, who served for more than a decade as the top staff 
officer of the California Assn. of Realtors until his retirement in 1989. 
Wiedmann was selected as executive vice president of the 140,000-member trade 
group in June, 1978, midway through his term as the association's president, a 
one-year elective office. 
</P>
<P>
He was the first official in the association's history to have served in both 
positions. Wiedmann began his real estate career in San Diego in 1960 after a 
10-year career with the Navy. He operated a general real estate brokerage 
company in the Mission Bay area of San Diego until moving to Los Angeles in 
1978. Under Wiedmann, the association established a series of education courses 
that real estate licensees must pass before renewing their licenses. In Los 
Angeles on Friday of the complications of cancer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
