<P>
MCDONALD'S RECYCLING PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dum . . . da-dum . . . dum . . . 
</P>
<P>
Headline -- April 14, Business section: "McDonald's Warns Press on Poison Ads"! 
Major newspapers come under fire for exposing fat content of McDonald's 
products; told to "check with company" before printing ad. 
</P>
<P>
Headline -- April 18, Business section: "McDonald's Will Buy Recycled Goods to 
Build Outlets"! Effort to appease food giant fails as attorney-founder of Earth 
Day condemns improvement, "If it is just for public relations." 
</P>
<P>
Headline -- April 19, editorial, "That Wonderful Big Mac Attack"! Public 
relations running smoothly at food giant as The Times reports that one-fourth 
of McDonald's self-beautification budget will "be used to buy recycled 
products." The Times calls McDonald's "responsible." 
</P>
<P>
Such are the days for the free press, public relations and free promotions. 
</P>
<P>
EDWARD T. BAGLEY 
</P>
<P>
La Puente 
</P>
