<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIXON LETTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I write to express my gratitude and appreciation for your readers of whom I am 
proud to be one. 
</P>
<P>
I was amazed and not a little disgusted at your giving a podium to Nixon and my 
final impulse was to say so. 
</P>
<P>
Then I thought of the wonderful letters writers and knew I could depend on them 
to come through once again. 
</P>
<P>
I was rewarded, more than I ever imagined -- 63 anti- and only two pro-Nixon 
letters! Wonderful! 
</P>
<P>
I hope you are properly chastened. 
</P>
<P>
MILDRED G. KRAMER 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
