<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
General Motors units: Detroit-based GM Hughes said its first-quarter profit 
fell 13% to $182.8 million as revenue dropped to $2.02 billion from $2.03 
billion. 
</P>
<P>
It cited defense spending cuts and a sharp drop in demand for automotive 
components. At Dallas-based Electronic Data Systems, first-quarter profit rose 
11% to $109.8 million as revenue climbed 10% to $1.42 billion. General Motors 
Acceptance Corp.'s income fell 6% to $336 million, which the Detroit unit 
attributed to lower financing income and earnings from insurance underwriting 
that offset lower borrowing costs. General Motors is to report overall results 
today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
