<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Book for Bookings: So you're ready to produce your performance, theater or 
dance piece but all the theaters are either too large, too small, or too 
expensive? The Los Angeles Festival's Open Festival and the Santa Monica-based 
Community Arts Resources Inc. have published the county's first venue guide. 
</P>
<P>
The $5 guide, which will be given free to the more than 1,100 artists who 
expressed an interest in participating in September's Open Festival, lists more 
than 450 spaces, ranging from community centers to the Hollywood Bowl. It is 
available from the Open Festival offices. Information: (213) 315-9444. GREG 
BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
