<P>
James Brown Shut Down: "Godfather of Soul" James Brown, recently freed from 
prison, won't be giving a concert later this month as he had planned. 
</P>
<P>
South Carolina corrections officials say a May 16 performance by Brown was not 
and will not be approved. "This looks like a commercial endeavor on the part of 
Mr. Brown and some of his associates . . . and does not fall within the scope 
of his job," said prison spokesman Francis Archibald. Brown, 56, was freed from 
prison and placed in a work release counseling job last month. BETH KLEID 
