<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: CARLSBAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man and a woman were found dead Wednesday in an apparent murder-suicide, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Derick Wesley White, 38, and Diana Lynn White, 43, were found about 6:30 a.m. 
in the master bedroom of a home in the 2700 block of Flower Fields Way, 
according to police. A handgun was found in the bedroom. 
</P>
<P>
A preliminary investigation revealed the incident to be a murder-suicide, 
police said, with both victims suffering gunshot wounds. The investigation is 
continuing. 
</P>
