<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: CHARGERS SIGN THREE ADDITIONAL FREE AGENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chargers announced the signing of three free agents Wednesday, adding to 
the five they signed a week ago following the NFL draft. 
</P>
<P>
They are: tight end Dave Colonna, 6-feet-5, 235 pounds, Duke; defensive end 
Mike Estes, 6-2, 220, Central Washington, and running back Jerry Mays, 5-7, 
173, Georgia Tech. 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
The University of San Diego announced that Chris Enger has been selected to 
play in the U.S. Olympic Festival in Minneapolis in July. Enger averaged 9.9 
points, 8.5 rebounds and 3.6 blocks and was the West Coast Conference's 
freshman of the year. 
</P>
<P>
Candida Echeverria, USD's all-time leading scorer with 1,211 points, was named 
the team's most valuable player for the second consecutive year, at the 
Toreras' banquet. Molly Hunter (defense), Christi English (most improved) and 
Angie Straub (hustle) were also honored. 
</P>
<P>
It was also announced that Coach Kathy Marpe has signed Ernestine Rose Platero 
of Cochise (Ariz.) Community College. Platero led Cochise (23-8) in scoring 
(15.0 average) and rebounding (8.0). 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State defeated Air Force, 5-1, and advanced to the final of the 
Western Athletic Conference Tournament championship. The top-seeded Aztecs play 
Utah today. Against Air Force, SDSU lost only three games, with Tole Marinkovic 
winning at No. 1 singles, 6-1, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
SENIOR TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
Liz Harper of La Jolla, seeded sixth in the women's 60s singles of the National 
Hardcourt Championship, defeated Muriel Bard of Laguna Hills, 6-0, 6-2. She and 
all other top-seeded players advanced to today's third round at the La Jolla 
Beach and Tennis Club. 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
Pitchers Debbie Corbett (Mesa College) and Deann Ford (Santana High), catcher 
Lisa Wilson (Chula Vista High) and shortstop Benna Kennedy (Fullerton High) 
have signed letters of intent to play at U.S. International. 
</P>
</TEXT>
