<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, ART OF DINING -- It was called the Art of Dining III. Nine chefs from 
around the world gathered at the Four Season's Hotel in Newport Beach to cook 
an eight course dinner for 450 patrons of the art. The event, which raised 
$250,000 to benefit the Newport Harbor Museum also included an auction of a 
1990 Jaguar convertible, a pair of Tiffany watches and a dinner for 12 by 
Joachim Splichal of Patina Restaurant in Los Angeles. The guests sat down to a 
synchronized meal which included eggplant caviar and caponata, timbale of 
salmon, smoked rabbit consomme, scallop roe in a potato crust, pasta with wild 
mushroom and truffle juice, roast foie gras in a corn crepe with Banyuls sauce, 
roast lamb chop wrapped in vegetable mousseline and three exquisite desserts. 
The chefs who worked together, contributing their talents to the dinner are, 
from left, Michel Pieton of the Four Seasons Newport Beach; Joachim Splichal; 
Debra Ponzek of New York's Montrachet, Christopher Gross of Christopher's in 
Arizona; Michel Galloyer of Le Trianon in Angers, France; Susan Spicer of 
Bayona in New Orleans; Pierre Herme of Fauchon in Paris; Hubert Keller of Fleur 
de Lys in San Francisco and Lorretta Keller of Stars in San Francisco. JOHN 
FUNG / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
