<HEADLINE>
<P>
HISPANIC JOURNAL RECEIVES ATTENTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harvard alumni and Southland Latino leaders met in Los Angeles recently to call 
attention to the publication of the Spring 1990 Journal of Hispanic Policy, an 
annual report on the progress of the Latino community by the Hispanic Students 
Caucus at Harvard University's John F. Kennedy School of Government. 
</P>
<P>
The publication is funded by corporate and individual contributions. Eight 
members of its 25-student staff are from Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
 Information, (617) 495-1311. 
</P>
<P>
