<HEADLINE>
<P>
110 LATINO YOUTHS ATTEND CONFERENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A quiet woods near the Malibu coast was the place to be for 110 Latino youths 
selected by a panel of educators to attend the Second Chicano/Latino Youth 
Leadership Conference, sponsored by the Los Angeles Board of Education and 
National Hispanic Arts, Education and Media Institute. 
</P>
<P>
The three-day conference, held in March at Camp Hess Kramer, enabled young 
people to meet a Latino journalist, educator and film producer, among others, 
and to receive training in civics, culture and contemporary issues. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call Katrina Blanco, (213) 969-2896. 
