<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SANTA PAULA; 
</P>
<P>
CHECKERS PLAYER HELD IN SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROLYN KUSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Santa Paula man who fired two gunshots at his checkers opponent was arrested 
Wednesday. No one was injured in the incident, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Rafael Magana, 24, was arrested on suspicion of attempted murder, Santa Paula 
Police Cmdr. Bob Gonzalez said. 
</P>
<P>
Magana and Magdaleno Sosa, 26, of Santa Paula began fighting in La Hacienda Bar 
in the 900 block of Main Street during a game of checkers, Gonzalez said. 
</P>
<P>
Magana fired a shot at Sosa, who ducked to avoid being hit by the bullet. A 
second shot fired at Sosa also missed, Gonzales said. 
</P>
<P>
Magana fled the bar but was arrested shortly after in a nearby street, Gonzalez 
said. Magana was being held Wednesday in Ventura County Jail in lieu of 
$250,000 bail, he said. CAROLYN KUSKY 
</P>
</TEXT>
