<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATIONAL PET WEEK WILL BEGIN SUNDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Happiness Is a Healthy Pet" is the theme of National Pet Week, which begins 
Sunday and is being sponsored by the Southern California Veterinary Medical 
Assn. 
</P>
<P>
According to association president Dr. Ronald S. Porter, responsible pet 
ownership requires providing food, shelter, love and proper health care, as 
well as obeying leash and licensing laws, vaccinating dogs and cats, and 
cleaning up after pets to "ensure better pet / community relations." 
</P>
<P>
Porter said that National Pet Week is also working to increase public awareness 
of the psychological and physiological benefits of pet ownership. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA050390-0107 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 213324 </DOCID>
