<P>
HUBBLE TELESCOPE HITS ANOTHER SNAG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An error by ground controllers triggered an emergency closure of the Hubble 
Space Telescope's aperture door and sent the observatory into hibernation for 
nearly 12 hours, NASA officials said. But project officials at the NASA Goddard 
Space Flight Center in Greenbelt, Md., reported that the $1.5-billion telescope 
was brought back to normal "quickly and effectively," in part because of the 
practice the controllers received during the telescope's problem-plagued first 
week in orbit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
