<P>
TOWN GRIEVES OVER TEEN-AGERS' SUICIDES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mourners of three teen-agers who killed themselves were told at the first 
victim's funeral in Sheridan, Ark., that it was too late to bring him back, but 
going with him was "still our choice." Thomas Smith, 17, was the first of three 
suicides among students at Sheridan High School in two days, and counselors for 
their classmates were on 24-hour call. About 250 people packed into a chapel to 
hear the Rev. Dennis Moon urge them to cling to God as they grieved over 
Smith's death. 
</P>
