<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: MONROVIA; 
</P>
<P>
CITY TO SPONSOR CLUB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Monrovia Aquatics Club will remain a city-sponsored program, at least for 
another 18 months, the City Council decided Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The Community Services Department had recommended that the 45-member club 
become independent, but a large turnout of supporters at City Hall Tuesday 
persuaded the council to continue subsidizing the club's activities for now, 
Councilwoman Mary Wilcox said. 
</P>
<P>
After 18 months, the city will evaluate whether the club should become 
independent, City Manager Jim Starbird said. Until then, the city will help pay 
for coaches and insurance, he said. Starbird said the city spends $2,500 or 
less each year to support the club's programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
