SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: IRWINDALE; 
</P>
<P>
MAYOR, VICE MAYOR ELECTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has unanimously elected Richard Chico mayor and Robert Diaz 
vice mayor. 
</P>
<P>
Both will serve one-year terms. 
</P>
<P>
Chico replaces former Mayor Salvador Hernandez, and Diaz replaces Patricio 
Miranda. Hernandez and Miranda remain on the council. 
</P>
<P>
After last Thursday's council vote, Chico said he wants to "reactivate" 
development and redevelopment in Irwindale, which slowed down for 2 1/2 years 
while the city tried unsuccessfully to land the Los Angeles Raiders. 
</P>
