<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: WEST HOLLYWOOD; 
</P>
<P>
300 TRY FOR DEPUTY POSTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 300 people showed up Saturday at Fairfax High School to take the initial 
test to become deputies for the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department, 
according to West Hollywood's Public Safety Officer Nancy Greenstein. West 
Hollywood officials had requested the test be given in the local area to 
encourage more gays and lesbians to consider careers in law enforcement. 
</P>
