<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: SOVIET UNION WINS ANOTHER WORLD HOCKEY TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Soviet Union, relying on an experienced lineup, defeated Czechoslovakia, 
5-0, to win a record 22nd World Hockey Championship Wednesday at Bern, 
Switzerland. 
</P>
<P>
The Soviet Union, which won its first title in its 1954 debut at Stockholm, 
completed the medal round with a 3-0 record, outscoring the opposition, 15-1. 
The Soviet team hasn't lost in a medal round since the 1985 tournament at 
Prague, when Mario Lemieux led Canada to victory. 
</P>
<P>
Sweden won the silver medal by beating Canada, 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Game Story; Wire 
</P>
