<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Steve Emmons and Cristina Lee 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CLEAN CAMPAIGN: UCI student elections officials expect all the campaign posters 
to be gone by Saturday afternoon, 48 hours after the end of voting. . . . Why? 
Because a candidate who doesn't comply could be disqualified, even after he's 
won. 
</P>
<P>
And no one will know the winners until Monday. . . . But is it legal? No, says 
attorney Dan Stormer, who successfully sued the university in 1985 to reform 
student election regulations. "It's ludicrous. It's election by intimidation," 
he says. Steve Emmons and Cristina Lee 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
<TYPE>
<P>
