ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Steve Emmons and Cristina Lee 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LEAK BUSTERS: Though the water shortage is not as serious here as in L.A. (A3), 
people are getting concerned. . . . Tim Downs, partner in a leak detection 
service in Santa Ana, says business has increased over the last six months, due 
mostly to homeowners worried about wasting water. . . . The worst household 
offender: the home swimming pool, whose underground plumbing can invisibly leak 
hundreds of gallons a day. "It's easy to think the water's just evaporating," 
Downs said. Steve Emmons and Cristina Lee 
</P>
