<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNINGSIDE'S LESLIE ELIGIBLE AS FRESHMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROB FERNAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lisa Leslie, Morningside High's All-American center, has scored over 700 on her 
third attempt at the Scholastic Aptitude Test, making her eligible to play 
collegiate basketball as a freshman next fall. 
</P>
<P>
The 6-foot-5 Leslie said she will take her final recruiting trip this weekend 
to Cal State Long Beach. She is also considering USC and Notre Dame. 
</P>
<P>
Leslie averaged 27 points, 15 rebounds and seven blocked shots a game last 
season. 
</P>
<P>
Leslie scored 101 points in a half against South Torrance this year. She was 
denied a chance at the national record of 105, set by Cheryl Miller of 
Riverside Poly in 1982, when South Torrance refused to play the second half. 
ROB FERNAS 
</P>
</TEXT>
