<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAVRATILOVA EASILY GAINS QUARTERFINALS OVER CUETO 6-2, 6-2 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HAMBURG, West Germany 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Martina Navratilova breezed past Isabel Cueto of West Germany 6-2, 6-2 today to 
reach the quarterfinals of the Citizen Cup women's tennis tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Navratilova won in 77 minutes, and was much sharper than in Wednesday's opening 
match Wednesday in which she dropped a set to Australian Rachel McQuillan. 
</P>
<P>
Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario of Spain, the No. 3 seed, cruised to a 6-2, 6-1 victory 
over 16th-seeded West German Sylvia Hanika; fifth-seed Helena Sukova downed 
fellow Czechoslovak Regina Rajchrtova 7-6, 6-2 and Judith Wiesner of Austria, 
the No. 8 seed, defeated West German Wiltrud Probst 6-3, 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
Navratilova was never in trouble against Cueto, who was slowed by an aching 
knee. 
</P>
<P>
"She wasn't able to move as well as she can and that took a bit of the wind out 
of her sails," Navratilova said. But I felt more comfortable today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
