<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
TEXAS COACH DRAWS SUSPENSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
AUSTIN, Tex. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Texas basketball coach Tom Penders has been suspended for one Southwest 
Conference game for his comments about the quality of league officiating. 
</P>
<P>
The ruling by SWC commissioner Fred Jacoby is subject to appeal, and Texas will 
exercise that option before the SWC Compliance Committee May 16 in Dallas, the 
Dallas Morning News reported. 
</P>
<P>
The suspension applies to the Longhorns' first SWC game next season, against 
Texas A&amp;M on Jan. 2 in Austin. 
</P>
<P>
Also, Penders and assistant coach Jamie Ciampaglio have been placed on 
probation for the entire season and any further criticism of SWC officials 
could result in future single- or multi-game suspensions. 
</P>
<P>
Penders criticized the officiating after Texas' loss to Houston in the 
semifinals of the SWC tournament March 10. Penders was reprimanded earlier by 
Jacoby for comments on the officiating in Texas' loss to Arkansas on Jan. 25 in 
Fayetteville. 
</P>
</TEXT>
